Ruby on Rails drives me nuts, and today I found another example of why: the cryptic error messages. After a server update, my chiliproject/redmine site refused to start. The error message was
 &ldquo;Object is not missing constant Issue!&rdquo;
 What does that even mean? It took me a little while to understand that Issue in this context is the Redmine object &ldquo;Issue&rdquo;. But still, &ldquo;Object is not missing constant X&rdquo; isn&rsquo;t much help.

